1801.definition: [ἐνωτίζομαι] middle voice from a compound of {{G1722}} and {{G3775}}; to take in one's ear, i.e. to listen

1802.definition: [Ἐνώχ] of Hebrew origin ({{H2585}}); Enoch (i.e. Chanok), an antediluvian

1804.definition: [ἐξαγγέλλω] from {{G1537}} and the base of {{G32}}; to publish, i.e. celebrate

1805.definition: [ἐξαγοράζω] from {{G1537}} and {{G59}}; to buy up, i.e. ransom; figuratively, to rescue from loss (improve opportunity)

1807.definition: [ἐξαιρέω] from {{G1537}} and {{G138}}; actively, to tear out; middle voice, to select; figuratively, to release

1809.definition: [ἐξαιτέομαι] middle voice from {{G1537}} and {{G154}}; to demand (for trial)

1810.definition: [ἐξαίφνης] from {{G1537}} and the base of {{G160}}; of a sudden (unexpectedly) Compare {{G1819}}.

1811.definition: [ἐξακολουθέω] from {{G1537}} and {{G190}}; to follow out, i.e. (figuratively) to imitate, obey, yield to

1812.definition: [ἑξακόσιοι] plural ordinal from {{G1803}} and {{G1540}}; six hundred

1813.definition: [ἐξαλείφω] from {{G1537}} and {{G218}}; to smear out, i.e. obliterate (erase tears, figuratively, pardon sin)

1816.definition: [ἐξανατέλλω] from {{G1537}} and {{G393}}; to start up out of the ground, i.e. germinate

1817.definition: [ἐξανίστημι] from {{G1537}} and {{G450}}; objectively, to produce, i.e. (figuratively) beget; subjectively, to arise, i.e. (figuratively) object

1819.definition: [ἐξάπινα] from {{G1537}} and a derivative of the same as {{G160}}; of a sudden, i.e. unexpectedly Compare {{G1810}}.

1820.definition: [ἐξαπορέομαι] middle voice from {{G1537}} and {{G639}}; to be utterly at a loss, i.e. despond

1821.definition: [ἐξαποστέλλω] from {{G1537}} and {{G649}}; to send away forth, i.e. (on a mission) to despatch, or (peremptorily) to dismiss

1822.definition: [ἐξαρτίζω] from {{G1537}} and a derivative of {{G739}}; to finish out (time); figuratively, to equip fully (a teacher)

1823.definition: [ἐξαστράπτω] from {{G1537}} and {{G797}}; to lighten forth, i.e. (figuratively) to be radiant (of very white garments)

1824.definition: [ἐξαυτῆς] from {{G1537}} and the genitive case singular feminine of {{G846}} ({{G5610}} being understood); from that hour, i.e. instantly

1825.definition: [ἐξεγείρω] from {{G1537}} and {{G1453}}; to rouse fully, i.e. (figuratively) to resuscitate (from death), release (from infliction)

1826.definition: [ἔξειμι] from {{G1537}} and εἶμι (to go); to issue, i.e. leave (a place), escape (to the shore)

1827.definition: [ἐξελέγχω] from {{G1537}} and {{G1651}}; to convict fully, i.e. (by implication) to punish

1828.definition: [ἐξέλκω] from {{G1537}} and {{G1670}}; to drag forth, i.e. (figuratively) to entice (to sin)

1829.definition: [ἐξέραμα] from a comparative of {{G1537}} and a presumed ἐράω (to spue); vomit, i.e. food disgorged

1831.definition: [ἐξέρχομαι] from {{G1537}} and {{G2064}}; to issue (literally or figuratively)

1832.definition: [ἔξεστι] third person singular present indicative of a compound of {{G1537}} and {{G1510}}; so also      ἐξόν neuter present participle of the same (with or without some form of {{G1510}} expressed); impersonally, it is right (through the figurative idea of being out in public)

1833.definition: [ἐξετάζω] from {{G1537}} and ἐτάζω (to examine); to test thoroughly (by questions), i.e. ascertain or interrogate

1834.definition: [ἐξηγέομαι] from {{G1537}} and {{G2233}}; to consider out (aloud), i.e. rehearse, unfold

1836.definition: [ἑξῆς] from {{G2192}} (in the sense of taking hold of, i.e. adjoining); successive

1837.definition: [ἐξηχέομαι] middle voice from {{G1537}} and {{G2278}}; to "echo" forth, i.e. resound (be generally reported)

1839.definition: [ἐξίστημι] from {{G1537}} and {{G2476}}; to put (stand) out of wits, i.e. astound, or (reflexively) become astounded, insane

1840.definition: [ἐξισχύω] from {{G1537}} and {{G2480}}; to have full strength, i.e. be entirely competent

1841.definition: [ἔξοδος] from {{G1537}} and {{G3598}}; an exit, i.e. (figuratively) death

1843.definition: [ἐξομολογέω] from {{G1537}} and {{G3670}}; to acknowledge or (by implication, of assent) agree fully

1844.definition: [ἐξορκίζω] from {{G1537}} and {{G3726}}; to exact an oath, i.e. conjure

1845.definition: [ἐξορκιστής] from {{G1844}}; one that binds by an oath (or spell), i.e. (by implication) an "exorcist" (conjurer)

1846.definition: [ἐξορύσσω] from {{G1537}} and {{G3736}}; to dig out, i.e. (by extension) to extract (an eye), remove (roofing)

1847.definition: [ἐξουδενόω] from {{G1537}} and a derivative of the neuter of {{G3762}}; to make utterly nothing of, i.e. despise See also {{G1848}}.

1848.definition: [ἐξουθενέω] a variation of {{G1847}} and meaning the same

1849.definition: [ἐξουσία] from {{G1832}} (in the sense of ability); privilege, i.e. (subjectively) force, capacity, competency, freedom, or (objectively) mastery (concretely, magistrate, superhuman, potentate, token of control), delegated influence

1851.definition: [ἐξοχή] from a compound of {{G1537}} and {{G2192}} (meaning to stand out); prominence (figuratively)

1854.definition: [ἔξω] adverb from {{G1537}}; out(-side, of doors), literally or figuratively

1856.definition: [ἐξωθέω]   or ἐξώθωfrom {{G1537}} and ὠθέω (to push); to expel; by implication, to propel

1860.definition: [ἐπαγγελία] from {{G1861}}; an announcement (for information, assent or pledge; especially a divine assurance of good)

1861.definition: [ἐπαγγέλλω] from {{G1909}} and the base of {{G32}}; to announce upon (reflexively), i.e. (by implication) to engage to do something, to assert something respecting oneself

1862.definition: [ἐπάγγελμα] from {{G1861}}; a self-committal (by assurance of conferring some good)

1863.definition: [ἐπάγω] from {{G1909}} and {{G71}}; to superinduce, i.e. inflict (an evil), charge (a crime)

1865.definition: [ἐπαθροίζω] from {{G1909}} and ἀθροίζω (to assemble); to accumulate

1868.definition: [ἔπαινος] from {{G1909}} and the base of {{G134}}; laudation; concretely, a commendable thing

1869.definition: [ἐπαίρω] from {{G1909}} and {{G142}}; to raise up (literally or figuratively)

1870.definition: [ἐπαισχύνομαι] from {{G1909}} and {{G153}}; to feel shame for something

1874.definition: [ἐπακροάομαι] from {{G1909}} and the base of {{G202}}; to listen (intently) to

1875.definition: [ἐπάν] from {{G1909}} and {{G302}}; a particle of indefinite contemporaneousness; whenever, as soon as

1876.definition: [ἐπάναγκες] neuter of a presumed compound of {{G1909}} and {{G318}}; (adverbially) on necessity, i.e. necessarily

1877.definition: [ἐπανάγω] from {{G1909}} and {{G321}}; to lead up on, i.e. (technical) to put out (to sea); (intransitively) to return

1879.definition: [ἐπαναπαύομαι] middle voice from {{G1909}} and {{G373}}; to settle on; literally (remain) or figuratively (rely)

1880.definition: [ἐπανέρχομαι] from {{G1909}} and {{G424}}; to come up on, i.e. return

1881.definition: [ἐπανίσταμαι] middle voice from {{G1909}} and {{G450}}; to stand up on, i.e. (figuratively) to attack

1882.definition: [ἐπανόρθωσις] from a compound of {{G1909}} and {{G461}}; a straightening up again, i.e. (figuratively) rectification (reformation)

1883.definition: [ἐπάνω] from {{G1909}} and {{G507}}; up above, i.e. over or on (of place, amount, rank, etc.)

1884.definition: [ἐπαρκέω] from {{G1909}} and {{G714}}; to avail for, i.e. help

1885.definition: [ἐπαρχία] from a compound of {{G1909}} and {{G757}} (meaning a governor of a district, "eparch"); a special region of government, i.e. a Roman præfecture

1886.definition: [ἔπαυλις] from {{G1909}} and an equivalent of {{G833}}; a hut over the head, i.e. a dwelling

1887.definition: [ἐπαύριον] from {{G1909}} and {{G839}}; occurring on the succeeding day, i.e. ({{G2250}} being implied) to-morrow

1888.definition: [ἐπαυτοφώρῳ] from {{G1909}} and {{G846}} and (the dative case singular of) a derivative of φώρ (a thief); in theft itself, i.e. (by analogy) in actual crime

1890.definition: [ἐπαφρίζω] from {{G1909}} and {{G875}}; to foam upon, i.e. (figuratively) to exhibit (a vile passion)

1891.definition: [Ἐπαφρόδιτος] from {{G1909}} (in the sense of devoted to) and Ἀφροδίτη (Venus); Epaphroditus, a Christian Compare {{G1889}}.

1892.definition: [ἐπεγείρω] from {{G1909}} and {{G1453}}; to rouse upon, i.e. (figuratively) to excite against

1893.definition: [ἐπεί] from {{G1909}} and {{G1487}}; thereupon, i.e. since (of time or cause)

1894.definition: [ἐπειδή] from {{G1893}} and {{G1211}}; since now, i.e. (of time) when, or (of cause) whereas

1896.definition: [ἐπεῖδον] and other moods and persons of the same tense; from {{G1909}} and {{G1492}}; to regard (favorably or otherwise)

1898.definition: [ἐπεισαγωγή] from a compound of {{G1909}} and {{G1521}}; a superintroduction

1900.definition: [ἐπέκεινα] from {{G1909}} and (the accusative case plural neuter of) {{G1565}}; upon those parts of, i.e. on the further side of
